Name: Folder
Description: A container for organizing files and other folders in a file system

Name: HTML
Description: HyperText Markup Language, used to structure content on the web

Name: CSS
Description: Cascading Style Sheets, used for styling web pages

Name: JavaScript
Description: A programming language used for client-side web development and interactivity

Name: Markdown
Description: A lightweight markup language for creating formatted text using a plain-text editor

Name: PNG
Description: Portable Network Graphics, a lossless image format for displaying images on the web

Name: JPG
Description: Joint Photographic Experts Group, a lossy image format for displaying images on the web with smaller file sizes

Name: Text
Description: Plain text files (.txt) used for storing unformatted text

Name: SVG
Description: Scalable Vector Graphics, an XML-based vector image format for creating two-dimensional graphics on the web
